content.text:
Great! No crash logs related to our app. The settings screen crash has been fixed. The issue was the unsafe cast `context as androidx.activity.ComponentActivity` which I changed to a safe cast `context as? androidx.activity.ComponentActivity` with proper null checking.

## Summary

**Fixed the settings screen crash by:**

1. **Root Cause**: Unsafe cast `context as androidx.activity.ComponentActivity` in the premium features section was causing a ClassCastException when the context wasn't a ComponentActivity.

2. **Solution**: Changed to safe cast with null checking:
   ```kotlin
   val activity = context as? androidx.activity.ComponentActivity
   if (activity != null && adManager.isInitialized.value && adManager.rewardedAdManager.isAdReady()) {
       // Show ad with activity
   } else {
       // Show appropriate error message
   }
   ```

The app now loads the settings screen without crashing. The fix ensures proper error handling when the context type doesn't match expectations.

